  "text": "All five artifacts located in the OpenJDK tree:\n\n1. **Provider.java** (`src/java.base/share/classes/java/security/Provider.java`) \u2014 abstract class `Provider` (line 113) with inner `public static class Service` (line 1500). Key methods: `getService()` (line 1136), `getServices()` (line 1183), and `Service.newInstance()` (line 1713).\n\n2. **Security.java** (`src/java.base/share/classes/java/security/Security.java`) \u2014 `public final class Security` (line 76) managing provider registration. Key methods: `addProvider()` (line 494), `insertProviderAt()` (line 469), `getProvider()` (line 548), `getProviders()` (lines 532/613/691).\n\n3. **SunJCE.java** (`src/java.base/share/classes/com/sun/crypto/provider/SunJCE.java`) \u2014 `public final class SunJCE extends Provider` (line 83). Note: this lives under `java.base` (not `java.crypto`).\n\n4. **Cipher.java** (`src/java.base/share/classes/javax/crypto/Cipher.java`) \u2014 `public class Cipher` (line 179). Factory method `getInstance()` at lines 538/637/707. Provider resolution via `getTransforms()` (line 452), `getTransform()` (line 476), `chooseFirstProvider()` (line 794), and `chooseProvider()` (line 899).\n\n5. **java.security** config (`src/java.base/share/conf/security/java.security`) \u2014 lists default providers at lines 96\u2013113 as `security.provider.tbd=<name>` entries (SUN, SunRsaSign, SunEC, SunJSSE, SunJCE, SunJGSS, SunSASL, XMLDSig, SunPCSC, JdkLDAP, JdkSASL, plus platform-specific SunMSCAPI/Apple/SunPKCS11).\n\nThe dependency chain flows: `Cipher.getInstance()` \u2192 `getTransforms()` \u2192 iterates registered `Provider`s via `Security.getProviders()` \u2192 calls `Provider.getService()` to find a matching `Service` \u2192 `Service.newInstance()` creates the `CipherSpi` implementation (e.g. from `SunJCE`).",
